plot missingness pattern by longitude and latitude \(H0\)

\(he\)

library(ggplot2)
PH_pollution <- read.csv("~/Downloads/PH_data/PH_pollution.csv")
pm25 = ifelse(is.na(PH_pollution$pm25),"missing","not missing")
AZ_latitude = PH_pollution$Latitude[which(PH_pollution$statecode=='AZ')]
AZ_longitude = PH_pollution$Longitude[which(PH_pollution$statecode=='AZ')]
CA_latitude = PH_pollution$Latitude[which(PH_pollution$statecode=='CA')]
CA_longitude = PH_pollution$Longitude[which(PH_pollution$statecode=='CA')]
missing_or_not_AZ = factor(pm25[which(PH_pollution$statecode=='AZ')])
missing_or_not_CA = factor(pm25[which(PH_pollution$statecode=='CA')])
qplot(AZ_longitude,AZ_latitude,colour = missing_or_not_AZ,main = "Arizona")

qplot(CA_longitude,CA_latitude,colour = missing_or_not_CA,main = "California" )

Missing values in California do not have obvious spatial pattern, but in Arizona, missing values are clustered at (32:34, 110:113).

poisson regression on missingness vs cases/primary

pm2.5 = ifelse(is.na(PH_pollution$pm25),0,1)
primary_pm25 = data.frame(PH_pollution$primary/PH_pollution$denom,pm25)
colnames(primary_pm25) = c("rates","pm25")
primary_pm25.glm = glm(rates ~ pm25, data = primary_pm25, family='quasipoisson')
summary(primary_pm25.glm)$coefficients
##                   Estimate Std. Error     t value     Pr(>|t|)
## (Intercept)     -9.5739440  0.4520341 -21.1796950 6.869660e-93
## pm25not missing  0.4193089  0.5063610   0.8280829 4.076895e-01

The coefficient associated with pm25 is not significantly different from 0. Thus theres no relationship between missingness and cases/primary (missing at random).

Thus, impute pm2.5/pmcoarse/pov/urc by taking the mean for Arizona (?) while remove missing data for California

newdata = PH_pollution
rows_to_delete = NULL
for (row in 1:nrow(newdata)){
        for (col in 1:ncol(newdata)){
                if (is.na(PH_pollution[row,col]) & PH_pollution[row,3]=="AZ"){
                        newdata[row,col] = mean(PH_pollution[,col],na.rm = T)
                }else if (is.na(PH_pollution[row,col]) & PH_pollution[row,3]=="CA"){
                        if (row %in% rows_to_delete == FALSE){
                                rows_to_delete = append(rows_to_delete, row)
                        }
                }
        }
}
newdata = newdata[-rows_to_delete, ]
head(newdata)
